df = read_csv('adult_census.csv')
df %>% filter(marital.status == "Divorced"|marital.status == "Widowed") %>% 
       ggplot(aes(x = sex,
                  fill=workclass))+
  geom_bar(position = 'fill')+
  transition_states(marital.status) +
  labs(title = 'Class: {closest_state}')

  1. Use the WHOs dataset at this link. Make a top-10 bar race by months between countries on the number of deaths by Covid 19 in 2021.
library(gapminder)
## Warning: package 'gapminder' was built under R version 4.3.3
library(gganimate)
library(ggplot2)
library(tidyverse)
library(lubridate)
library(knitr)
df = read_csv('https://covid19.who.int/WHO-COVID-19-global-data.csv')
df <- df %>% filter(Cumulative_deaths>0,Date_reported>"2021-01-01",Date_reported<"2022-01-01")
df$month <- month(df$Date_reported)
d1 <- df %>% group_by(month, Country) %>% summarise(mean = mean(Cumulative_deaths))
d2 <- d1 %>% group_by(month) %>% mutate(rank=rank(-mean)) 
d3 <- d2 %>% filter(rank <= 10)
a1 <- d3 %>% ggplot(aes(x=rank, y=mean, group=Country, fill=Country, label=Country)) + geom_col()+
    geom_text(aes(y = mean, label = Country), hjust = 1.4)+ 
    coord_flip(clip = "off", expand = FALSE) +scale_x_reverse()+
    labs(title = 'Week {closest_state}', x='', y='Total Number of Deaths', fill='Country')+
    theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 1, size = 22),
          axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
          axis.text.y  = element_blank()) + 
    transition_states(month)+
    ease_aes("cubic-in-out")
animate(a1, nframes = 400)

  1. Make a bar race using a dataset of your own interest. You may use the dataset that we use in class (https://covidtracking.com/data/download/all-states-history.csv) but you should make a different bar racev from ones in the slides.
library(gapminder)
library(gganimate)
library(ggplot2)
library(tidyverse)
library(lubridate)
library(knitr)
df = read_csv("https://covidtracking.com/data/download/all-states-history.csv")
## Warning: One or more parsing issues, call `problems()` on your data frame for details,
## e.g.:
##   dat <- vroom(...)
##   problems(dat)
df <- read_csv('https://covidtracking.com/data/download/all-states-history.csv')
## Warning: One or more parsing issues, call `problems()` on your data frame for details,
## e.g.:
##   dat <- vroom(...)
##   problems(dat)
df <- df %>% filter(deathIncrease>0, positiveIncrease>0)
library(lubridate)
df$week <- week(df$date)
d1 <- df %>% group_by(week, state) %>% summarise(mean = mean(deathConfirmed))
d2 <- d1 %>% group_by(week) %>% mutate(rank=rank(-mean)) 
d3 <- d2 %>% filter(rank <= 10)
a1 <- d3 %>% ggplot(aes(x=rank, y=mean, group=state, fill=state, label=state)) + geom_col()+
    geom_text(aes(y = mean, label = state), hjust = 1.4)+ 
    coord_flip(clip = "off", expand = FALSE) +scale_x_reverse()+
    labs(title = 'Week {closest_state}', x='', y='Total Number of Confirmed Deaths', fill='state')+
    theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 1, size = 22),
          axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
          axis.text.y  = element_blank()) + 
    transition_states(week)+
    ease_aes("cubic-in-out")
animate(a1, nframes = 400)
